The Berserker Guild

Berserkers are warriors who refuse to let pain remain merely pain. Injury,
pressure, and a hard fight build Fury. At its peak, that Fury breaks loose
as Frenzy: a rapid series of attacks that empties the Berserker's rage into
whoever is standing in front of them.

Fury is not the only danger. A Berserker who learns to hold back Frenzy can
turn excess rage into Madness. Madness makes the Berserker harder and more
violent, but each step gives up another measure of control. The "bvent"
command can clear Fury and Madness once the fighting has stopped.

At Madness 4, each main-hand attack can gain extra swings. Most surges add one,
but increasingly rare rolls add two, three, or four at once. Momentum mastery
improves every tier of that long-tail chance, and Madness 5 improves it again.
Uncontrolled bonus rounds are non-reentrant and are not generated by Frenzy
pulse rounds, preventing either mechanic from recursively multiplying combat.
Madness 5 also leaves the Berserker Exposed and, outside combat, deals 2% of
maximum health every ten seconds until the Madness subsides. A strong Black
Scar reduces that self-damage. Use "berhelp madness" for the exact chances and
the effects of every Madness level.

Berserkers follow their own course of advancement. Combat earns Berserker
Rank, and each Rank grants one Vex. Vex can be spent through "vex train" to
deepen the Blood, Momentum, and Defiance branches. Every branch contains
both active abilities and lessons that change how those abilities behave.
Use "vex tree" to see the path ahead. Hunting across varied areas keeps
combat awards strongest; bosses are exempt from this hunting adjustment.

Once a branch has been completed, further Vex can be placed into its
mastery. Mastery has no final rank. Its greatest combat gains come early,
while later ranks stand as a record of dedication.

Scars mark the fights a Berserker has survived. They are permanent once
earned. With the Flare ability, one scar can be awakened for a short time.
Use "scars" to review the marks carried on your baldric. An awakened scar
appears as Flared Scar in the "buffs" display while at full strength.

Each scar remembers a different ordeal: Blood comes from victory while badly
wounded, Iron from enduring brutal blows or control, Packbreaker from winning
while heavily outnumbered, Frenzy from carrying a frenzy through several
kills, and Black from pushing Madness to its limit. These are hints rather
than exact formulas; the "scars" command repeats them when needed.

The scars command also explains their effects. Blood converts part of damage
dealt into healing, Iron improves weapon and control resistance, Packbreaker
rewards fighting several enemies, Frenzy adds one or two pulses to a Frenzy,
and Black reduces Madness 5's out-of-combat self-damage.

Enrage costs 8% of maximum health, falling to 6% at rank 3. Blood Price still
rewards fighting below 35% health, but at Blood Price rank 3 Enrage receives
that Fury bonus at any health. Thick Hide grants its listed base weapon
resistance while Mad and scales to twice that value at 25% health or lower.

The "berskills" command lists active abilities, their commands, current
costs, cooldowns, and Vex training. "berskills available" shows only the
abilities already trained. Help for a particular command is available
through "berhelp <command>".

Every Berserker also knows several core techniques outside the Vex tree.
Vent spends SP to force accumulated rage away. Incite creates a timed effect
that trades SP for a stream of Fury during combat. Wildrage wakes a temporary
chaos proc in the main weapon for three to ten minutes depending on level.
Heave spends SP on a Constitution-assisted, weight-driven weapon strike that
can damage a breakable weapon; Sheave trades some damage to strike safely with
a worn shield.

Berserkers may use light, medium, or heavy armour, including shields. Type
"berhelp armour" for details about guild and item restrictions.

Other useful commands include:

  bstatus                    Review Rank, XP, Vex, resources, and active states
  frenzymode                 Choose automatic or directed Frenzy
  berserk, ber <message>     Speak on the Berserker guild channel
  berserkers, bers           List active Berserkers
  bhist [lines]              Review recent guild conversation

The Darkwind trainer handles joining, experience conversion, and Vex
retraining. "convert berserker <normal-xp|next>" trades normal experience
for Berserker experience. "retrain vex confirm" refunds trained Vex for an
escalating coin fee without removing Rank, scars, or other lasting progress.
